nd Michael Cunningham, arguing for the novel's distinct power in rendering the devastation of 9/11.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAmerican fictiony21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPsychic trauma in literature. 0aSeptember 11 Terrorist Attacks, 2001xInfluence. 0aSeptember 11 Terrorist Attacks, 2001, in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/vers1493640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231520331423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231520331/original  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK